		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper08</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Metamodel Family for Role-Based Modeling and Programming Languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ThomasKühn.html">Thomas Kühn</a>, <a href="../profile/MaxLeuthäuser.html">Max Leuthäuser</a>, <a href="../profile/SebastianGötz.html">Sebastian Götz</a>, <a href="../profile/ChristophSeidl.html">Christoph Seidl</a>, <a href="../profile/UweAßmann.html">Uwe Aßmann</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_8">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_8</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> It designs a family of language metamodels capturing role-based modeling/programming concepts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The work is grounded in metamodeling as a metalanguage for specifying families of related languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It relates modeling and programming perspectives, supporting integration across technical spaces.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagL">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It characterizes constraints/properties of roles (e.g., well-formedness) that amount to static semantics.
</li></ul></li></ul>
